 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-LOOP-3: Learning Loop 3 (Ontology Discovery/OBSERVER-6) partially closed -- shallow feedback only. Observation: LIVE -- braid observe embeds each observation, assign_to_concepts_soft() matches against concepts. At harvest, crystallize_concepts() runs agglomerative clustering. Analysis: LIVE -- O(n^2) clustering, TF-IDF names, variance computation, split/merge detection. Feedback: SHALLOW -- concepts feed routing via concept_dampening() (routing.rs:906) which deprioritizes well-observed areas. But concepts do NOT: (1) create new schema attributes (no ontology categories). (2) propose new boundary definitions (no structural feedback). (3) modify ISP classification. (4) feed into hypothesis ledger. Also: DOGFOOD-2 scored 3.48/10. The hash embedder produces deterministic but semantically poor embeddings -- this is a FIXABLE implementation issue (Model2Vec via embeddings feature flag exists and is implemented), not architectural. SOLUTION: (1) Enable Model2Vec embeddings by default (fix concept quality). (2) When concept variance stays below threshold for N sessions, propose new boundary connecting concept entities to existing boundaries. (3) Feed concept stability metrics into hypothesis ledger for calibration. VERIFICATION: After Model2Vec enabled, rerun DOGFOOD-2 scoring. Verify concept quality improves above 6/10. DEPENDENCIES: Quality fix (Model2Vec) is independent. Boundary proposal depends on AUDIT-C8-7 (dynamic boundaries)."
